data.title: + St George’s Singers [Poynton]
data.meta_description: ‘Formed in Poynton, Cheshire in 1956 with 23 founding members drawn from the local community.
data.text: ‘Formed in Poynton, Cheshire in 1956 with 23 founding members drawn from the local community. Today, the Choir has over 100 members who travel from Cheshire, Derbyshire, Yorkshire and Greater Manchester, and is widely recognised as one of the most enterprising and innovative choirs in the North of England.’
